Common CV mistakes that you may have come across:
- including all tasks in your previous experience
- making your CV longer than two pages
- not adding references (or saying something like: references available upon request)
- using the same CV for every job application

If you're applying for jobs and not getting any response or any calls for interviews then most probably the issue is with your CV

Now last but not least, know that you attract what you feel, if you feel you're not getting a job then you won't. I won't turn this into a religious post, but BELIEVE that if you're positive about this and anticipating your dream job? You will get it

Good luck all!

Don't forget to modify your approach based on each company, also modify your CV as well, it's always better to have a CV for each position you're interested in

Applying for posted jobs won't get you anywhere, you have to CREATE your own position following this approach

Remember that you getting a job is because you are benefiting their business, and because they need you. Not because they're doing you a favor

Many people don't check their DM's, so don't worry if you get no reply at all, trust the process (and stay focused!)

Avoid sending weird msgs like (hi) and wait for a reply, this freaks EVERYONE out. Start a conversation with the previous tweet (modify it as you see fit) and do this for 5 people from 5 companies every day, and let go once you send the msg, don't wait for their reply

Introduce yourself in a friendly yet professional manner highlighting your qualifications (SUMMARIZE), explain why you're interested in THIS SPECIFIC COMPANY, what your career goals are and how you'd love to achieve them with their team

Now it's time to reach out to employers, approach AT LEAST 5 people from each company that are decision makers, avoid HR, talk directly to those who know they need you (mostly project managers, team leaders and directors)

This is how I suggest you do this:

Every business, every company and every "good" decision maker would love to hear about what you are offering to their workplace

It's never about you, no one cares about what you've been through and how much you need a job, they really couldn't care less so be careful here

Now that your LinkedIn profile is ready, your CV is perfect, you're active and engaging on the platform, and you're connected to as many decision makers as possible, prioritize the list and choose 5 companies DAILY to apply for, i'll explain how

Be active, comment, post professional posts (especially these that share a story)

ALWAYS be positive about your past experience NO MATTER HOW TERRIBLE IT WAS.. you don't want ANYONE to know you've been treated badly as this gives them the impression they can do the same to you

search for people working in these companies, filter them so you only see people working in UAE, CONNECT with managers, regional directors, team leaders and project managers from this company

Send as many connection requests as you want! they're lucky to connect with u :)

This helps recruiter know you're open for jobs (even if you're currently employed but looking for something better)

Now remember that list of 20 companies? keep it with u for the next step

In your LinkedIn "About", list ALL the skills you have that are directly related to the jobs, you want the recruiter to know you're actually fit for the job

In your headline, mention a number of positions (up to 3), i.e.: Civil Engineer || Planning Engineer || Data Analyst

Your LinkedIn profile needs to be well-organized, avoid using scanned weird photos

make sure you're easily searchable and your URL is modified (remove the weird numbers from your URL!) this is how: https://t.co/RXpSBGy59p

Understand why you truly want this job in this company, don't think of salaries here, believe me I know people who're getting paid A LOT and they're in the process of quitting due to the terrible work atmosphere

write your own list, to the tiniest detail, you need them written

First things first, you need a polished CV that is ATS friendly, and you should submit it in a word format

and a list of companies you are interested to work in, write a list up to 20 companies, GO BIG with your dreams, that's alright!
